{"article_id":"G1IkNaYsxXiRHPxx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The revelation","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"Hillary Rodham Clinton used an off-the-books email account during her time as secretary of state","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"reverberated across Washington on Tuesday ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"further eroding the Obama administration ' s claims of transparency ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"giving new momentum to House Republicans","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"investigating the Benghazi affair","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"and raising fresh questions about Mrs. Clinton ' s credibility","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"heading into 2016 .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"While Mrs. Clinton now has turned over roughly 55,000 pages of emails","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"- including about 300 messages","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"related to the deadly September 2012 terrorist attack in Benghazi","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"given to House Republicans -","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"it ' s unclear whether more emails remain hidden and , if so , how many .","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"Rep. Trey Gowdy , South Carolina Republican and head of the House Select Committee on Benghazi , said","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"the private account has helped Mrs. Clinton avoid answering questions about the terrorist attack","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that claimed four American lives ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"as well as the administration ' s actions in the aftermath of that attack .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"\" We ' ve been asking [ the State Department ] for months and months and months for certain emails ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"and we just now find out","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"that those emails were never going to be produced","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"because they don ' t have custody of them , \"","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Mr. Gowdy said .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"\" Right now we are in a position","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"of having to go to her or her attorneys","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"to ask for work","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that was done on behalf of the American people .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"The records custodian should be at the State Department .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"The records custodian should not be in her private law firm . \"","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Experts say","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"the case of Mrs. Clinton is perhaps the most egregious example to date of the administration","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"failing to live up to its own lofty promises about transparency .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"\" It ' s pretty stunning , \"","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"said John Wonderlich , policy director at the Sunlight Foundation ,","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"which advocates for open government .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Hillary Clinton email shenanigans help skirt Benghazi probe :","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"Gowdy","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"Mr. Wonderlich added","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"the case of Mrs. Clinton may be worse than other instances , such as former Environmental Protection Agency Administrator Lisa Jackson","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"using the alias \" Richard Windsor \"","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"to mask her identity during email conversations ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"or former IRS official Lois Lerner","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"using a private account for official business .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"\" Not only is it higher-profile ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"but","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"if the claims","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"made are right ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"then it is more pre-calculated and apparently applied to all of her emails , \"","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"\" That level ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"I think ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"is deeply unusual .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"\" As for motivation , you have to assume","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"it is to avoid political and professional risk .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"She wants to control access to her information ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"and the people","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"who manage access to it","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"are her employees \" at the State Department , \"","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Mr. Wonderlich said .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"The New York Times first reported Monday night","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"that Mrs. Clinton , the clear front-runner for the Democratic presidential nomination , did not use a government email address during her four years","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"running the State Department .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"Instead , she conducted all official correspondence through a private account ,","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"leading to possible violations of federal record-retention requirements ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"creating possible security risks","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"and fueling speculation","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"that the former first lady has something to hide .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Mrs. Clinton ' s spokesman , Nick Merrill , said","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"the former secretary complied with the \" letter and spirit \" of the law","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"and had \" every expectation \"","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"that all of her emails","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"related to State business","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"would be retained by the department .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"On the political front , the potentially damaging news comes","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"just as Mrs. Clinton gears up for her expected 2016 presidential campaign .","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"It also comes on the heels of unrelated revelations","depth":5},{"id":76,"text":"that the Clinton Foundation accepted millions of dollars in donations from foreign governments","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"while Mrs. Clinton ran the State Department .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"Republicans are putting pressure on Mrs. Clinton to release all of her emails in what they say","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"would be a desperately needed display of openness ,","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"and are outraged by the fact","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"that State Department employees ,","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"who reported to Mrs. Clinton ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"were in charge","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"of cataloging all emails .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"\" Transparency matters , \"","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"2016 GOP presidential contender and former Florida Gov . Jeb Bush tweeted Tuesday ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"drawing attention to a website","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"he ' s established","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"solely for housing years ' worth of his own emails .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"\" Unclassified @ HillaryClinton emails should be released .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"You can see mine , here , jebbushemails.com , \"","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"he continued .","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"Outside groups already are taking steps","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"to bring all of Mrs. Clinton ' s emails to light .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"The America Rising PAC ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"which describes itself as dedicated to \" exposing the truth about Democrats , \"","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"filed a Freedom of Information Act request Tuesday for all messages","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"sent from State Department employees to Mrs. Clinton ' s private address .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"The group highlighted other concerns","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"raised by critics and pundits :","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"Private email is not as well protected","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"and is more susceptible to hacking .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"\" It is the responsibility of the State Department to release these emails , \"","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"the PAC ' s executive director , Colin Reed , wrote in a letter to the State Department .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"\" We understand","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"that any classified correspondence","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"sent to her private email","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"can be exempted by this request ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"though the Chinese government probably has it now . \"","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Legally , it appears Mrs. Clinton was operating in something of a gray area .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"Since the Presidential and Federal Records Act was amended last year ,","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"all government officials","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"conducting any business on private accounts","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"must forward the emails to their government inbox within 20 days .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Before those new rules went into effect ,","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"the National Archives and Records Administration recommended","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"that official accounts be used","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"but did not require it ,","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"provided the department or agency in question took steps","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"to make sure","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"all emails were preserved .","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"\" We have reached out to the State Department","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"to ensure","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"that all federal records are properly identified and managed in accordance with the Federal Records Act","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"and that controls and procedures are in place","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"to manage records effectively in the future , \"","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"Paul M. Wester , the federal government ' s chief records officer , said in a statement .","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"State Department officials say","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"they formally requested Mrs. Clinton ' s private emails as part of a larger records-gathering project","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"stretching all the way back to Madeline Albright ' s days as secretary of state under President Clinton .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"The Clinton camp says","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"it was more than willing to help with that project .","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"\" When the department asked former secretaries last year for help","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"ensuring their emails were in fact retained ,","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"we immediately said ' yes , ' \"","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"Mr. Merrill said .","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"The State Department also says","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"it has \" long had access to a wide array \" of Mrs. Clinton ' s emails ,","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"including messages","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"sent to department employees","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"using a state.gov address .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"But it ' s not yet clear","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"whether the department has a full and complete record of all relevant emails","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"sent by Mrs. Clinton .","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"The White House ,","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"while encouraging officials to use government accounts ,","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"it does not believe","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"Mrs. Clinton was trying to conceal anything .","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"\" We think","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"if people choose to conduct government business on email ,","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"that they should do so","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"using their official government account , \"","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"White House press secretary Josh Earnest told reporters .","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"\" Based on what we know about what Secretary Clinton ' s team did ,","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"they succeeded in that effort","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"in making sure","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"that those records were properly preserved and maintained ,","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"and we have some evidence","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"to back that up ,","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"in that hundreds of those records","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"we know","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"have been turned over to Congress in response to legitimate oversight inquiries , \"","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"As for the Benghazi investigation , Mr. Gowdy said","depth":7},{"id":167,"text":"that the committee has received some emails from Mrs. Clinton","depth":8},{"id":168,"text":"that have aided the probe .","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"But investigators have no way","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"of knowing","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"whether they have all the records","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"that they have requested","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"beyond assurances from Mrs. Clinton and her attorneys ,","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"he said .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":349,"left":233,"right":348,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":202,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":182,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":177,"right":181,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":176,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":176,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":3,"right":180,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":178,"right":179,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":178,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":186,"right":200,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":185,"right":12,"relation":"adversati